{
  "texts": [
    "Recorded characters are exclusively used in 3DoF experiences, and predominantly in Passive ones, which explains the higher usage of characters for Passive experiences.",
    "Audio formed part of 70% of the reconstructions, of which 36% was Ambient, 20% Narration, 10% Sound effects, and 4% Music, the least common category.",
    "Within iVR experiences, there were no clear patterns regarding audio usage, except for Music that was exclusive to Explorative and Explorative interaction iVR experiences.",
    "Similar to characters, the extensive use of audio in Passive experiences was attributed to its significant use in 3DoF experiences, where Passive was the type of iVR with the highest audio usage.",
    "Finally, interface usage was employed in 59% of experiences, where 24% was PoI, 18% Panel, and 17% Menu."
  ]
}